==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electro-thermancy
<hw>E*lec`tro-ther"man*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That
branch of electrical science which treats of the effect of an electric
current upon the temperature of a conductor, or a part of a circuit
composed of two different metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-tint</ent>⟦br⟧
